# BTC Scalping Strategies for MT5 Expert Advisors

## Executive summary

BTC remains liquid enough for scalping, but the current market still demands wider and more disciplined stops than many retail ŌĆ£ultra-tightŌĆØ crypto scalpers use. As of todayŌĆÖs market snapshots, BTC is trading around USD 61.7k, with roughly USD 4.67bn of spot volume, about USD 59.74bn of futures volume, and open interest near USD 45.15bn. Recent volatility norms are also still large by traditional macro or FX standards: DeribitŌĆÖs 15-day historical volatility is about 32.65% annualised, while CMEŌĆÖs real-time 30-day implied volatility index is about 45.40%. ŅłĆciteŅłéturn18search1Ņłéturn18search2Ņłéturn4search0Ņłéturn2search1Ņłü

Those volatility numbers imply that BTCŌĆÖs ŌĆ£normalŌĆØ noise on short horizons is not trivial. A rough square-root-of-time conversion gives about 0.35% to 0.49% for a one-hour one-sigma move and roughly 0.10% to 0.14% for a five-minute one-sigma move. In practice, that means stops materially tighter than about 0.08% are often brittle unless your spread is very small and execution is excellent. The four strategies below therefore aim for aggressive-but-practical stop bands, use regime filters, and assume account size is **unspecified**, so all sizing is expressed as a percentage of equity rather than fixed lots. ŅłĆciteŅłéturn16calculator1Ņłéturn16calculator2Ņłéturn17calculator0Ņłéturn17calculator1Ņłéturn4search0Ņłéturn2search1Ņłü

The framework is intentionally regime-based. The strongest research anchors here are that Bitcoin has shown exploitable intraday mean-reversion tendencies on some horizons, trading-range breakout rules have shown forecasting power in Bitcoin, and large technical-rule universes can still beat buy-and-hold on a risk-adjusted out-of-sample basis ŌĆö but higher-frequency profitability becomes much more vulnerable to costs. That is why the strategy set below includes one trend pullback model, one range-fade model, one volatility breakout model, and one trend re-entry model, each with explicit spread and slippage safeguards. ŅłĆciteŅłéturn14view2Ņłéturn12search1Ņłéturn26view0Ņłü

## Market context and assumptions

Recent market structure is heavily derivatives-led. CoinGlassŌĆÖs current BTC snapshot shows futures volume far exceeding spot volume and open interest still elevated, which is consistent with a market where liquidation cascades and momentum bursts can still matter intraday. Separately, recent research using one-minute BTC/USDT data highlights volatility clustering and heavy tails in minute-level Bitcoin behaviour, which is one reason ATR-based or structure-plus-ATR stops are more robust than fixed tiny tick stops. ŅłĆciteŅłéturn18search2Ņłéturn11view2Ņłü

For MT5 implementation, the key unit is **points**, not ŌĆ£pipsŌĆØ. MetaTrader exposes the symbol point value through symbol properties, along with spread, tick size, tick value, and minimum stop distances. The exact point size therefore depends on your brokerŌĆÖs BTC symbol specification. The examples in this report assume a **0.01 point** quotation **only for illustration**. At BTC 61,657.4, a 0.10% move is about USD 61.66, which equals roughly 6,166 points if `SYMBOL_POINT = 0.01`; a 0.20% move is about USD 123.31, or roughly 12,331 points under the same assumption. Use the general conversion  
`price_distance = entry_price ├Ś percentage` and `points = price_distance / SYMBOL_POINT`. ŅłĆciteŅłéturn28search1Ņłéturn21search7Ņłéturn18search1Ņłéturn22calculator1Ņłéturn23calculator1Ņłü

I also favour **bar-close entry confirmation** on M1, M3 or M5 rather than pure tick-chasing. Bitcoin intraday research finds microstructure effects at very short horizons and more meaningful mean-reversion structure at higher intraday intervals; meanwhile, cost-aware studies show higher trading frequency is the area most likely to lose robustness once transaction costs rise. In MT5 terms, that means your EA can use `OnTick()` for order placement and trade management, but the actual signal engine should usually be gated by a completed-bar check on the entry timeframe. ŅłĆciteŅłéturn11view1Ņłéturn14view2Ņłéturn26view0Ņłéturn7search1Ņłü

